body:
Oh well, that is Obj C, and apparently a kind which won’t and cannot work on older macOS.

@HannahShiSFB Since you have initially committed https://github.com/grpc/grpc/commit/24e158d5a93f0471dae89ad44b1c442148943e59 – could we make it conditional, excluding it for some macOS versions? I am not sure of exact threshold, but looks like on 10.6 and earlier this won’t build.

If this file defines what is included, then dropping `cf_engine` from the generic case (why is it even needed there?) may fix at least PowerPC build:
https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/4e41ec6f1f82fdb8a7e96fa0afa6192534ca79df/src/core/BUILD#L2238-L2249

UPD. No, this does not change anything.

The minimum support macOS version is 10.12 now, this is not only for gRPC but its dependencies as well, such as Protocol Buffers, BoringSSL, etc.

You can give it a try by adding a mac_ppc? config (no idea whether bazel supports it) with only posix_event_engine, or removing all the mac ones so they default to posix_event_engine.

If you are using cmak or makefile, you'll most likely need to run `./tools/buildgen/generate_projects.sh` after changed the BUILD file.

@HannahShiSFB All dependencies build fine for us at least back to 10.5.8 on all archs, including PowerPC (we have the latest compilers on all systems: GCC for PowerPC, Clang and GCC for Intel). `gRPC` has been building too – the only trouble now is Obj C code, and unfortunately it is something not easily fixable, if at all. Not for me, at least.

I build with CMake, yes.
Can you try if #34061 works for you?

It looks like you're trying to build and run the CFEngine on Mac, for Mac, which I thought was not intended @HannahShiSFB. IIRC, the CFEngine is only expected to build & run on iOS, and Macs should be using the PosixEventEngine. I am guessing this is a build configuration error. @sampajano please take a look as well.
@drfloob I mean, I did not specifically try to build it; apparently, some defines are inaccurate, and configure gets this wrong.

CFEngine is enabled in Mac for fast development iteration and more test coverage, it's built on Mac but not enable for production use (unless explicitly override the default event engine factory).
In #34061 I'm trying to exclude the build for older Mac OS versions, however looks like it's still missing something

issue.title: [ObjC] require osx version > 10.12 for cf event engine
